race.comment: Tricky. ZA ZA BEST (8) is a Savabeel 3yo who improved sharply when beaten a whisker at Wangaratta over 1590m. He's an improving galloper ready for the step up to the middle distance. Meech is aboard today and is likely to position. Wary of FURTHEREST POINT (1)  resuming over the 2015m for the Michael Kent stable. He placed over a mile at Seymour on debut and was immediately tipped out. He will be naturally improved and has two jumpouts under the saddle. One of Australia's best jockeys is engaged, and that's a decent push for his chances. VALDA WARRIOR (13)  made good improvement placing up to this distance at Ballarat on a wet track. He's a chance. LYTTELTON (2) had this first middle distance go in the same contest, finishing a touch behind the above. Draws inside again. Any cut out of the ground would advantage this pair.
